title: Domasmï
preface: Domasmï is a mountain range in the South-East. It was inhabited by the Domaþund during The Age of Races, as well as a a Human population that have inhabited the mountains since The Age of Races until The Age of Awakening.

title: Domasmï
body:
Locations

  • Cathedral of the Dead (where dead Domakings are buried) 1xwg5n & dark-fantasy-art & i7uoMky
  • Castle of the Gorge (where a powerful Doma lives) 5-Yb86bf
  • The Floating Fortress (includes waterways inside) 13ocy8 & chris-cold-cw09
  • The Molten Monument (religious shrine) dark_fortress_by_jjcanvas & RXvqBWt & sflsynu & SsuMStVwl & ytP6wAwGCO

  • The Acropolis (Shrine) OKw-EYDQ5
  • The Claw Towers (row of defensive towers) yPQ9QStb

Notable Ћuman Locations

  • The Western Castle (first Domma-Human castle North of Domasmï) 1BpaLi
  • Martello 1 castle_by_artofjokinen
  • The Domma Shrine (place for humans to pay tribute to Doma) ia0NKG-y
